(137, 1, '2017-05-11 09:05:18', '2017-05-11 09:05:18', 'From now till 13th November 2016, you can enjoy a meal accompanied by adorable Craftholic characters! This cafe was possible thanks to the joint effort of Craftholic Singapore and Kki Sweets. Singapore is the first city to have a Craftholic cafe outside of Japan.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-140\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Craftholic-Cafe-Food.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1026\" />\r\n\r\nvia <a href=\"http://thehungrygeek.com/2016/09/20/craftholic-cafe-plushies-japan/\">The Hungry Geek</a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-141\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Craftholic-Cafe-Cake.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\" />\r\n\r\nvia <a href=\"http://mitsueki.sg/2016/09/22/craftholic-cafe-opens-singapore-17-sept-13-nov-2016/\">mitsueki</a>\r\n\r\nLocated at School of the Arts, Singapore (SOTA), you can visit this Craftholic themed cafe and be expected to see cute displays of the Craftholic character soft toys. Get ready to snap lots of photos of the cute desserts and meals that will be decorated with the characters. Fans can also buy limited edition collections and the new Otona Craft series by Craftholic.\r\n\r\nIn addition, Craftholic members get a 10% discount off their meal when you present your card.\r\n\r\nYou won’t want to miss out this super cute and special cafe. Go down today!\r\n\r\n<strong>Where:</strong> School of the Arts (SOTA), #02-01, 1 Zubir Said Drive, Singapore 227968\r\n<strong>When:</strong> From 17th September 2016 till 13th November 2016\r\n<strong>Hours:</strong> 11.30am to 9.30pm daily', 'Craftholic Cafe Exists and It’s in Singapore!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'craftholic-cafe-exists-and-its-in-singapore', '', '', '2017-05-11 09:05:35', '2017-05-11 09:05:35', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/?p=137', 0, 'post', '', 0),
