(194, 1, '2017-05-17 08:46:37', '2017-05-17 08:46:37', 'Are you a fan of Mango Sticky Rice and Thai Milk Tea? Well listen up because the Royal Thai Embassy is bringing back its Thai Festival this coming weekend! From Thai Food to Thai Fashion – it is as authentic as it can get. That’s not all, there will also be cultural performances like Muay Thai and Thai cooking shows put on just for you guys! Save on a plane ticket to Thailand and pop by Orchard this weekend to be a part of this exciting festival.\r\n\r\nThe Royal Thai Embassy is also offering an exciting chance for you to win a pair of THAI Airways tickets by just spending $20 on Thai products at the festival. Didn’t get your fare share of Thai goodies at Artbox because of the crowd? Fret not because here’s your chance to experience it all again. Post a photo on Instagram with the hashtag #ThaiFestSG to stand a chance to win a pair of Bangkok Airways tickets to Samui! These don’t even cover a fraction of the exciting prizes to be won, head down now so you won’t miss out on these goodies.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, entry is FREE for all so grab all your friends and enjoy a fun-filled weekend at Thai Festival 2017. Do check out our post tomorrow for a preview of the delicious Thai Boat Noodles that will be featured at this festival. This is only one of the many traditional Thai dishes available at the festival so do head down to find out more.\r\n\r\nDate : 4-7 May 2017\r\nTime : 10 AM – 9 PM\r\nVenue : Royal Thai Embassy, Orchard Road (MRT Orchard)\r\nEntry Fee : None\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Thai Festival 2017', 'Are you a fan of Mango Sticky Rice and Thai Milk Tea? Well listen up because the Royal Thai Embassy is bringing back its Thai Festival this coming weekend! ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thai-festival-2017', '', '', '2017-05-17 08:46:37', '2017-05-17 08:46:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/?post_type=what-to-eat&#038;p=194', 0, 'what-to-eat', '', 0),
