(197, 1, '2017-05-17 08:51:03', '2017-05-17 08:51:03', '“<strong>Dookki</strong>” means two meals in Korea and one would start the first meal with a Korean hotpot style, and end off with kimchi fried rice. This is the concept which the restaurant lives by. For only <strong>$18.80++</strong>, one gets to enjoy a tteokbokki buffet with an unlimited serving of rice cakes, noodles, fried food and drinks.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-208\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/top-view.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nFirst, you would create your own sauce concoction, based on your spicy preference. There’s even a guide provided.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/menu.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nNext, the sauce can be poured into the soup stock. As the stock boils, you can use the metal bowl to collect the rice cakes, noodles and vegetable ingredients.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-206\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/soup.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nThere are 8 types of tteok (rice cakes), from traditional tteok to sweet potato or cheese ones. The most common type of tteok is the long cylindrical rice cake sticks, which absorbs the tteokbokki sauce better. The most interesting one are the cheese tteok, which would ooze out the cheese fillings when they get boiled.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/ricecake.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nThere are even different types of noodles to choose from, other than ramyeon.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-205\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/ricecake.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nAfter boiling all the ingredients in the soup, you would get a Korean army stew like this!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/noodles-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nAfter our first meal, we proceeded with cooking our fried rice. The sauce left behind by the army stew would become starchier as it was boiled longer. It can then be used to fry the fried rice. The fried rice is prepared by frying the sauce, kimchi, corn and sesame oil.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/mee.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nFor cheese-lover fans out there, there’s even a <strong>double cheese ring</strong> for dipping at the price of <strong>$9.80++</strong>!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/kichi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nThere are also fried side dishes like sweet potato, fishcake, chicken etc. The best part is the Eomuk station where you can get hot sticks of boiled Korean fishcake boiled. You can even adjust the broth with the soy sauce at the side. It is a very fun and interesting experience if you have not been to Korea before!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cheese-ring.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nLastly, if you still have space for a third meal, you can choose from the wide array of ramyeon!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/fishcakes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nWe thoroughly enjoyed ourselves at Dooki and it is a unique experience you would never forget!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/ramen.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Address:</strong> 3 Temasek Boulevard, #B1-107, Singapore 038984\r\n<strong>Opening hours:</strong> Daily 11am to 10pm\r\n<strong>Tel:</strong> 6266 2425', 'Dookki: Singapore’s First Tteokbokki Buffet', 'For only $18.80++, one gets to enjoy a tteokbokki buffet with an unlimited serving of rice cakes, noodles, fried food and drinks.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dookki-singapores-first-tteokbokki-buffet', '', '', '2017-05-17 08:51:47', '2017-05-17 08:51:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/?post_type=what-to-eat&#038;p=197', 0, 'what-to-eat', '', 0),
