ng all the ingredients in the soup, you would get a Korean army stew like this!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/noodles-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nAfter our first meal, we proceeded with cooking our fried rice. The sauce left behind by the army stew would become starchier as it was boiled longer. It can then be used to fry the fried rice. The fried rice is prepared by frying the sauce, kimchi, corn and sesame oil.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/mee.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nFor cheese-lover fans out there, there’s even a <strong>double cheese ring</strong> for dipping at the price of <strong>$9.80++</strong>!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/kichi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nThere are also fried side dishes like sweet potato, fishcake, chicken etc. The best part is the Eomuk station where you can get hot sticks of boiled Korean fishcake boiled. You can even adjust the broth with the soy sauce at the side. It is a very fun and interesting experience if you have not been to Korea before!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cheese-ring.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nLastly, if you still have space for a third meal, you can choose from the wide array of ramyeon!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/kopifolks/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/fishcakes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\nWe thoroughly enjoyed ourselves at Dooki and it is a unique experience you would never forget!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/ko